# Graph Types

## Bar / Column Charts

+------------+---------------------+
| Renderers  | Google              |
+------------+---------------------+
| Graph Type | `bar` / `column`    |
+------------+---------------------+
| Data Modes | plain, group, pivot |
+------------+---------------------+

A bar or column chart shows values plotted as the length of a block which corresponds to a bucket of data.

### Configuration Options

* `categoryField` : string (plain mode only)

  Name of the field which gives the category (i.e. "bucket") of the box.  In column / vertical graphs, this is the x-axis value; in bar / horizontal graphs, this is the y-axis value.  The "display text" of the corresponding column in the grid overrides the field name in the axis label.

* `valueField` : string (plain mode only)

  Name of the field which determines the size of the box.  In column / vertical graphs, this is the y-axis value; in bar / horizontal graphs, this is the x-axis value.  The "display text" of the corresponding column in the grid overrides the field name in the axis label.

* `options` : object

  Additional configuration which is passed directly to the renderer.  See the [Google Charts documentation](https://developers.google.com/chart/interactive/docs/gallery/columnchart#configuration-options) for a complete list.

## Gantt Charts

+------------+---------+
| Renderers  | Google  |
+------------+---------+
| Graph Type | `gantt` |
+------------+---------+
| Data Modes | plain   |
+------------+---------+

A Gantt chart shows tasks on a timeline.  Each task is a row in the data.

### Optional Features

* Dependency relationships can be drawn between tasks.
* Tasks can be shown with a completion percentage.

### Limitations

* Gantt charts cannot be exported (saved as an image).  The renderer library does not offer it.

### Configuration Options

* `idField` : string

  Name of the field that acts as the ID for the task represented by that row.  If unspecified, a fake ID is generated for each row automatically.

* `nameField` : string (required)

  Name of the field that acts as the name or label for the task represented by that row.

* `resourceField` : string

  Name of the field that acts as a resource (method of grouping tasks) identifier for the task.

* `startField` : string

  Name of the field that gives the start date for the task.  The type of the field must be a date or datetime.

* `endField` : string

  Name of the field that gives the end date for the task.  The type of the field must be a date or datetime.

* `durationField` : string

  Name of the field that gives the duration of the task.  The type of the field must be a number.

* `options` : object

  Additional configuration which is passed directly to the renderer.  See the [Google Charts documentation](https://developers.google.com/chart/interactive/docs/gallery/ganttchart#configuration-options) for a complete list.

#### Notes

* Between the start, end, and duration, some values can be derived from others.  Thus, you don't need to provide all three.  The following configurations are allowed:

  - start + end
  - start + duration
  - end + duration
  - duration
